<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="399" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123.G35/58.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-23">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">September</hi> 23, 1912</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Cuban Secretary of State requests that Bell and I reply to written
                            interrogatories to be sent the Legation from the Audiencia. I request
                            that authorization be granted.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>